<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She never puts a foot wrong with fashion. </p>

<p>So it was no surprise to see Isla Fisher looking effortlessly chic as she ran errands in Los Angeles on Wednesday. </p>

<p>The Australian actress, 44, opted for a boho vibe as she teamed a maxi dress with chunky sandals. </p>

<p>Dressed to impress: She never puts a foot wrong with fashion. So it was no surprise to see Isla Fisher looking effortlessly chic as she ran errands in Los Angeles on Wednesday</p>

<p>Isla looked radiant in a white Tory Burch smock that featured navy embroidery along the sleeves and hemline. </p>

<p>Keeping her accessories simple, she slung a brown handbag over her shoulder, and subtly boosted her petite frame with chunky white sandals. </p>

<p>The mother-of-three swept her famous auburn tresses back into a bun and accessorised with a pair of gold hooped earrings and wayfarer shades - opting for a plain white face mask.  </p>

<p>Chic: The Australian actress, 44, opted for a boho vibe and looked radiant in a white Tory Burch smock that featured navy embroidery along the sleeves and hemline</p>

<p>Isla found fame starring on Home and Away before landing roles in several Hollywood blockbusters, including Confessions of a Shopaholic and The Great Gatsby.  </p>

<p>Isla currently has three films in post-production, Blithe Spirit, Godmothered and Unplugging - but fans will no doubt be keen to see if she's landed a role in the surprise Borat sequel.   </p>

<p>Isla has been married to comedian and filmmaker Sacha Baron Cohen, 48, since 2010 and back in 2016 they collaborated on his action comedy, Grimsby. </p>

<p>Sacha's most famous film, Borat is now set to get a sequel - which has already been filmed and screened for 'a select few industry types,' according to a new report from Collider.</p>

<p>Cohen, 48, had previously revealed in 2007 that he was planning to retire both his Borat and Ali G characters, though it seems he had a change of heart. </p>

<p>The sequel reportedly follows Cohen's Borat, who, after the release of the 2006 Borat film, thinks he's a huge movie star.</p>

<p>He tries hiding from the public, interviewing people while taking on different alter-egos along the way.</p>

<p>One source described the meta sequel as, 'Cohen playing Borat playing Cohen.'</p>

<p>One to watch: It was revealed this week that Isla's husband Sacha Baron Cohen secretly filmed a sequel for his famous film Borat, which has already screened for 'a select few industry types'</p>
